   I have a 52 mage and soon I'll be dueling a 52 ranger for a scheduled competition coming up in an arena-  Unfortunately I may end up not being able to use my pet... however we may be able to-  It's not decided yet.  I have not dueled much and I have been reading the posts here and have found some valuable information.  However, nothing specific about ranger versus Mage.  I am afraid that without my pet I am going to be for lack of better words, screwed!  Could any of you wise folk give me some tips for:<br>
<br>
1. How to duel a ranger best with a pet::<br>
a) what pet is best used?<br>
b) any clickable items that I should stock up on afore hand (I'm not rich or overly uber so I'm a little limited)<br>
c) what spells should I use: <br>
d) should I be running around much at all and when?<br>
<br>
2.  dueling a ranger without a pet:<br>
is there really no hope?<br>
what tactics could I try in that situation?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ularanos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laranos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(12/15/01 11:03:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage vs Ranger duel- need some tips!</span><hr size=1> Well, coming from Tallon Zek, I'll tell you what I can, and address your concerns on a case by case basis.<br>
<br>
1. a. You are level 52, which means you are lacking your level 54 water pet. This leaves you with two choices. Earth: More hp, potential root. 49 Fire: Hits hard, hits fast, and if the ranger turns to face it, Dshield rips him up.<br>
<br>
    b. Farm golem wands in CT. Something you can do very easily, it is a 5 charge instant cast wand with strip enchantement. That's the one that wipes out 4 buffs at a time from your target. That's the big one. Otherwise, cure poison potions might be nice.<br>
<br>
    c. I would have the following nukes up. Scintillation (fast casting, decent damage), Char (High damage, more mana efficient). I would have anull magic up, so you can keep your pet snare-free, without burning charges of your wand. Malosi should be in there of course, but if you don't land it within 2 casts, stop bothering to try. I would have a backup pet casting spell up, if he turns on your pet, and manages to remove it from the fight somehow, dismiss the pet and summon a new one. Depending on the terrain, I'd also have an invis up, evasion helps a lot, especially if it lets you heal a little with your phantom armor spell, and get a new pet. Oh, and of course, keep yourself damage shielded. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
     d. Should you be running? HELL YES. You need to evade damage as much as possible, while letting your pet deal as much as it can. Use the terrain as much as you can, duck around him, do anything to get out of the attack range of his weapons for as long as possible. The only time you should stand still is if you have the room to cast char, to null yourself, or for the 3 seconds it takes to cast scintillation. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2. Yes, if you don't have your pet, you can still beat him, but expect it to be a very long fight. Use lots of invis, damage shields, and evasion to take potshots, get out of the way, nuke from long distance, and sit down to regen and med as much as possible. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uniesei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Niesei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#333333>(4/20/02 12:16:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage vs Ranger duel- need some tips!</span><hr size=1> Wand of Swords from PoH. Easy to get, 3 charges of shock of swords, instant cast. Bam Bam Bam = Dead Ranger. Of course they are lore, and he will probably call that cheating. And use char if you have to. Scinilation is right, its a fast cast spell and does good damage. Good luck. <p>Niesei Fyresage<BR>52'nd Elementalist<BR>Brell Serilis<BR>
<img src=http://fyresage.freewebspace.com/images/niesig3.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzyare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zyare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(4/22/02 6:51:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage vs Ranger duel- need some tips!</span><hr size=1> I also play on tallon, and few things I've learned about fighting melees...<br>
<br>
1. lev rings.  come off hills to lev in mid air and nuke.  you will get a decent shot before he gets too close or you sink too low.  but from that elevated position (depending on how high), you should be able to get off a (I'm gonna catch flames for using this word) bolt.  since you're elevated, it should land.  course, if he starts plinking you for decent dmg, you may have to scratch that idea.  some call it cheating, but you are using your tools and the terrain to your advantage.  it's not like you are using an  exploit in the game.  just your summoned items. btw, keep your levitation way down the lists of buffs, all you need is for him to dispell it and you fall for 100+ dmg.<br>
<br>
2. staff of runes.  instant cast cancel magic, you never know when this might save your butt, especially with a snaring class. it's lore, but it might just save you.<br>
<br>
3. if you don't have epic, be sure to give your pet all those mr gear pieces. should make a difference is his ability to root and snare your pet.  as you are well aware of I'm sure, your pet is your life blood. if he's neutralized, you soon will be too.  on a ranger, I prefer to send the pet in and just keep summon pet memmed.  summon pet breaks root (the pet's, not yours).  I would use fire or water pet.  cause inevitably he is gonna get rooted or snare at some time in the fight if it lasts very long, the DDs will still be hitting him.  I've never had an earth pet root stick on anyone within 4 lvls of me with any sort of respectable mr (100+) without a tash.  I wouldn't waste any time with it.  go for the dmg, cause most people know better than to attack pet.<br>
<br>
anyways, those are some of the things I use when fighting rangers. I don't always win, but I usually fair pretty well.  more often than not, I send them running, no kill either way.  hope some of that you find usable. <p>Zyare - SR</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zeem>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#333333>(5/2/02 10:52:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ?</span><hr size=1> How on earth do you beat a L60 ranger with a good bow and a crapload of Alt-exp points?<br>
